nodes.bodyText:
That's weird since it is in x-pack and shouldn't need to specify the license. It is probably more likely that the new plugin needs (if not already there)

esplugin {
  extendedPlugins = ['x-pack-core']

or possibly
dependencies {
  javaRestTestImplementation project(path: xpackModule('core'), configuration: 'testArtifacts')
}

or possibly
dependencies {
  javaRestTestImplementation project(path: xpackModule('core'))
}

Fine to check it in as-is, I can take a look afterwards.

That is generally the preferred pattern, but either should work and we can move things around as needed later too.
